{{Infobox scientist|name = Derrick Pitts
|residence = [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]
|field = [[Astronomy]]
|work_institutions = [[Franklin Institute]]
|alma_mater = [[Saint Lawrence University]]
}}

'''Derrick H. Pitts''' is an [[United States of America|American]] [[astronomer]]. He is Chief Astronomer and Planetarium Director for the [[Franklin Institute]] in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]].<ref>[http://www2.fi.edu/exhibits/permanent/bloomobservatory.php The Franklin Institute]\</ref> He has been named as one of the 50 most important [[African-American]]s in research science.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20081022071630/http://www.sciencespectrumonline.com/artman/publish/article_3.shtml Science Spectrum Online]</ref> He was the president of the Philadelphia chapter of the [[Tuskegee Airmen, Inc]].<ref>[http://tuskegeeairmen.org/explore-tai/tai-chapters/ Tuskegee Airmen, Inc. Chapters]</ref> He has made numerous television appearances, including shows such as ''[[The Colbert Report]]'',<ref>[http://www.colbertnation.com/the-colbert-report-videos/223140/march-30-2009/derrick-pitts Colbert Nation]</ref> ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]'',<ref>[http://www.theinsider.com/videos/2289530_Craig_Ferguson_Derrick_Pitts_06_17_09 The Insider]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> ''[[Countdown with Keith Olbermann]],'' ''[[The Last Word with Lawrence O'Donnell]],'' and ''[[The Ed Show]]''. Since 1991, he's co-hosted a weekly radio discussion program called ''Skytalk'' on [[WHYY-FM]]<ref>[http://www.whyy.org/91FM/skytalk.html SkyTalk][[WHYY-FM]]</ref> in Philadelphia, PA.

Dr. Pitts is a graduate of [[Germantown Academy]]  ([[Fort Washington, PA]]), [[St. Lawrence University]], ([[Canton, NY]]) and has received honorary Doctor of Science degrees<ref>[https://www.fi.edu/scientists/derrick-pitts-hond Derrick Pitts, Hon.D | The Franklin Institute]</ref> from [[La Salle University]] (Philadelphia, PA), and Rowan University College of Mathematics and Science.<ref>D.H.Pitts</ref>

