The [[radio]]communication division of the [[International Telecommunication Union]] uses the following '''letter codes''' to identify its member countries. Eight countries are assigned single-letter codes ({{flag|Brazil|name=B}}, {{flag|Germany|name=D}}, {{flag|Spain|name=E}}, {{flag|France|name=F}}, {{flag|Great Britain|name=G}}, {{flag|Italy|name=I}}, {{flag|Japan|name=J}}, {{flag|Sweden|name=S}}), while the rest have [[Comparison of IOC, FIFA, and ISO 3166 country codes|codes three letters in length]]. The names of the countries are shown as mentioned in the [https://www.itu.int/online/mm/scripts/gensel8 ITU's official list].
