{{distinguish|magic word}} {{for|the formula used to divide the seven executive seats of the Swiss Federal Council|magic formula}} {{multiple issues|{{Refimprove|date=June 2010}}{{rewrite|date=February 2017}}}}
A '''magical formula''' is generally a word whose meaning illustrates principles and degrees of understanding that are often difficult to relay using other forms of speech or writing.{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}} It is a concise means to communicate very abstract information through the medium of a word or phrase.{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}} In the human practice of [[magic (paranormal)|magic]] a [[magic spell]] is used or "cast" by saying it in the proper fashion or context (in [[magic (gaming)|gaming]], by a character generally called a "[[Spellcaster (character class)|spellcaster]]").
These words often have no intrinsic meaning in and of themselves.{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}} However, when deconstructed, each individual letter may refer to some universal concept found in the system that the formula appears.{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}} Additionally, in grouping certain letters together one is able to display meaningful sequences that are considered to be of value to the spiritual system that utilizes them (e.g. spiritual hierarchies, historiographic data, or psychological stages).{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}} Many can be understood only by using various literal [[Hermetic Qabalah|Qabalistic]] techniques such as [[gematria]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}}
==Formulae==
*'''[[Abracadabra]]''' a common [[incantation]] used by [[stage magicians]] and used in ancient times as a cure for fevers and inflammations. *'''[[Abrahadabra|ABRAHADABRA]]'''. This formula, used by author and [[occultist]] [[Aleister Crowley]], is the Word of the [[Aeon (Thelema)|Aeon of Horus]] and represents the accomplishment of the [[Great Work]]. *'''[[Agape|AGAPE]]'''. A Greek word meaning "Love," whose enumeration in Greek [[isopsephy]] equals 93. *'''[[AGLA]]'''. Hebrew name of God constructed through [[notariqon]]. *'''[[Elohim|ALHIM]]'''. This is a spelling of [[Elohim]], a Hebrew name of God—or "Gods" in this case, since the spelling makes the name a masculine plural of the feminine noun. According to Crowley, it is a formula best used for consecration, since it "is the breath of benediction, yet so potent that it can give life to clay and light to darkness."<ref>Crowley, ''[[Magick (Book 4)]]'', p.155</ref> *'''AUMGN'''. Augmented form of the Sanskrit [[mantra]] [[Om|Aum]]. *'''[[Babalon|BABALON]]'''. A [[Babalon|goddess]] in [[Thelema]], whose name means "Gate of the Great God ON" according to ''Liber Samekh''. *'''HRILIU'''. used in [[Liber XV, The Gnostic Mass]] *'''[[Demiurge|IAO]], [[Abraxas]]'''. ΙΑΩ [[Isis]] Apophis [[apep]] [[Osiris]] *'''[[Tetragrammaton|IHVH]]'''. See YHVH. *'''INRI'''. {{Hebrew|ינרי}} Yod, Nun, Resh, Yod. Hebrew translation of the Christian [[Jesus, King of the Jews]] formula,<ref>777 p. 16-23</ref><ref>p. 37(30) Repletion</ref><ref>sepher sephiroth</ref> This magical formula represents the passing of life to death and [[Resurrection]], Used in many rituals including the [[Rose Cross]] and [[the Lesser Ritual of the Hexagram]] by both [[O.T.O]], [[A∴A∴]] and the [[Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn]],<ref name="Regardie1971vIIp204">The golden dawn, v. III p. 308</ref> see also [[deminuge|IAO]], [[Abraxas]] ΙΑΩ, *'''[[IPSOS]]'''. the word of the [[aeon of Ma'at]] other spellings include IPSOSh, IPShOS, IPShOSh from ''[[Liber Pennae Praenumbra]]'' by [[Nema (occultist)|Nema]].<ref>MAAT MAGICK p. 107</ref> *'''[[Jahbulon|JAHBULON]]'''. *'''LVX'''. Lit.= Latin word; Lux, or light. Part of the formula of the, "analysis of the key word," used in the [[Adeptus Minor]] ritual of the Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn, in which it is described in a ritualized manner,<ref name="Regardie1971vIIp204"/> linking each letter with an Egyptian [[Godform]]. Perhaps most popularized amongst the occult community at large by being included as the opening part to the [[Lesser Banishing Ritual of the Hexagram]] in [[Donald Michael Kraig]]'s bestselling book, "Modern Magick," (Llewellyn Publications, 1989.)<ref name="Kraig1989p27">Kraig (1989), p. 168.</ref> "LVX," may also be used as a closing to a letter, in the same manner as the word, "Sincerely," amongst initiates of some [[ceremonial magic]] orders. *'''MVAVM'''. Neophyte word and formula according to [[Frater Achad]]. *'''ON'''. Looks like the [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] name for [[Heliopolis (Ancient Egypt)|Heliopolis]], from an original meaning "pillar" or "pillars". This city claimed to hold the [[benben|Primeval Mound]] where [[Atum]] (sometimes identified with the mound) created the world.<ref>Utterance 600 in the Pyramid Texts, quoted at http://www.philae.nu/akhet/NetjeruA.html#Atum {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081220200810/http://www.philae.nu/akhet/NetjeruA.html |date=2008-12-20 }} retrieved November 9, 2006</ref> By Crowley's numeration, ON equals the Hebrew word [[Samekh#Hebrew Samekh|Samekh]] (a prop or support), which also serves as the name of a Hebrew letter.<ref>''[[Sepher Sephiroth]]'' for the number 120, in ''777 and other Qabalistic Writings of Aleister Crowley''.</ref> *'''[[Tetragrammaton|YHWH]]'''. The formula [[Tetragrammaton]] refers to the four-letter Hebrew name of God, [[Jehovah]], or Yod, He, Waw, He (יהוה). These letters have been attributed to numerous four-part symbols, including the classic elements, cardinal directions, [[Tarot]] suits, and so on. The formula is often represented by the Father (Yod) joining with the Mother (He), to produce the Son (Waw) and the Daughter (He-final). Within [[Yoga]] it is possible to see this formula as describing the union of the subject and the object to produce the exalted state of mind and the resulting ecstasy.<ref>Crowley, ''[[Eight Lectures on Yoga]]'', "First Lecture"</ref> Within a [[Thelemic]] framework, the first letter can also be interpreted as the original creative force, or [[Hadit]], who "marries" the eternally fertile, co-equal female force, [[Nuit]], resulting in the twins, [[Ra-Hoor-Khuit]] and Hoor-Par-Kraat (both of whom make up the deity [[Heru-ra-ha]], perhaps meaning "Horus and Ra be Praised!"). There are many other uses of this formula within the realm of mysticism. *'''VIAOV'''. Thelemic variation of IAO whose enumeration using gematria equals 93. *'''VITRIOL''' ''''Visita Interiora Terrae Rectificando Invenies Occultem Lapidem'''' (Visiting the interior of the Earth, rectifying comes the Occult Stone). Ancient alchemical formula.
